    "description": "If you're a passionate Reservation Manager with drive and ambition, Beyond Wildlife India Asia Pacific Associates in Srinagar is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Beyond Wildlife India Asia Pacific Associates:\nBeyond Wildlife India Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n• Coordinate with travel agents and OTAs for occupancy optimization\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Manage reservations and optimize room revenue through yield management\n• Monitor F&B service quality and maintain hygiene standards\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in PMS Systems\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n• Proficiency in Barista Skills\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n• Proficiency in Front Office\n• Proficiency in Food Safety\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Learning & development budget\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Beyond Wildlife India Asia Pacific Associates!",
